This paper discusses the issue of academic publishing and open access, which falls under the domain of digital libraries (cs.DL). It also touches upon information retrieval (cs.IR) as it discusses the dissemination of scientific knowledge. The paper also mentions the financial aspects of academic publishing, which could be categorized under cryptography and security (cs.CR) and cybernetics (cs.CY). Finally, the paper advocates for self-archiving, which could be considered a form of social and information networks (cs.SI).
